🥭Capri’s Wellness Smoothie🍐

I was diagnosed with pancreatitis about 2 years ago. Which started my skin issues & weight problem. I literally tried everything to get my body back healthy again. Like I went from 118 to 145 in about a month & couldn’t get the weight off to save my freakin life. I was always nauseous and had severe stomach pain after I ate. It was a struggle and I was so upset at myself because I caused it. Pancreatitis is cause by drinking too much alcohol. In my 20s I was running from life & used alcohol to keep a smile on my face instead of going to therapy. Then recently I started drinking this smoothie every morning along with other diet changes. Now I am 126! 😬 I don’t have breakouts anymore, I don’t have stomach pain at all, I’m not constipated anymore, and I am no longer nauseous after eating. This smoothie really changed my life so I hope this helps change someone else’s.🙏 

Mango🥭

Mangos has high vitamins C content that helps support your body’s natural collagen production. It also helps prevent sun damage and premature aging.

Pears🍐

Promote gut health and has anti-inflammatory properties which helps me with my pancreatitis. It also Helps lower your risk for diabetes and help with weight loss.

Papaya Juice🧋

Papaya juice Is rich in a certain enzyme called papain which increases collagen production. It also contains vitamins A, B, and C. Papaya helps with weight loss, clears dead skin cells, improves vision, boost immunity, fights cancer, and restores hormonal balance.

Kale🥬

Kale has vitamin A ( important for eye, bone health and a strong immune system), Folate, a B vitamin (key for brain development), Alpha-linolenic acid (An omega-3 fatty acid) vitamin C, vitamin K, and beta-carotene. It contains nutrients that can support weight management, heart health, eye health, and more. #fyp #foryoupage #betterubetterlife #pancreas #healthyrecipes #healthyfood
